There's a type of very hushed/quiet, calm female voice you hear a lot in older Soviet movies from the 70s that irl I have only seen in female patients with like psychiatric issues, mentally feeble who can't spell their name etc. and now any time I hear it in a film I am disturbed

I guess it was a cultural thing like how some Japanese women make their voices childlike, but the association it has for me now makes me unnerved, upset. I prefer aggressive foid voices that sound like they deeply despise me and talk to me like a noblewoman to an idiot barbarian.
